{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645015"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:11:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:11:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18075"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18075"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.04,0.11,0.64,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10789"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76267"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10789"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18075"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61771"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5737"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25143"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25994"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26111"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76267","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76267"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA newly graduated medical intern is working in the emergency department. A patient presents with a complex cardiac condition requiring advanced interventional procedures. From the intern\u0027s perspective, the appropriate scope of practice should be applied.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate action for the intern?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arrange direct specialist referral","Defer assessment until senior review","Document limitations and transfer care","Perform initial assessment then seek supervision","Request telephone advice from cardiology"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eperform initial assessment then seek supervision\u003C/strong\u003E. Medical practitioners have an ethical and legal obligation to work within their scope of practice, which is determined by their level of training, experience, and competence. When faced with situations beyond their capabilities, they must seek appropriate supervision and assistance while still providing essential initial care within their competence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument limitations and transfer care\u003C/strong\u003E may delay urgent care and does not fulfil the duty to provide initial assessment\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest telephone advice from cardiology\u003C/strong\u003E is inadequate for complex cardiac cases which require direct senior assessment\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArrange direct specialist referral\u003C/strong\u003E inappropriately bypasses emergency department senior staff and proper supervision pathways\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefer assessment until senior review\u003C/strong\u003E could compromise patient safety by delaying basic evaluation that is within scope\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWorking within scope of practice ensures patient safety and appropriate standards of care. It also protects practitioners from potential legal liability that could arise from practising beyond their level of competence.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical practitioners must only provide care within their level of training, experience and competence.","Scope of practice is determined by qualifications, training, experience, and credentialling by healthcare institutions.","Working outside scope of practice can result in patient harm and legal liability for the practitioner."],"references":["Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia. Medical Board of Australia. Updated 2024. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/Codes-Guidelines-Policies/Code-of-conduct.aspx?_gl=1*1imm9nu*_ga*MzYzODczMjE1LjE3MDQ5Nzk3NDM.*_ga_F1G6LRCHZB*MTczNTM4Mzk2My4xMC4wLjE3MzUzODM5NjMuMC4wLjA."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61771"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18075"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61771"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-02T16:59:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-02T17:00:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10789"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76267"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving in